<Author>globetrotter666
<Content>Great experience I recently stayed at this hotel for a total of 2 nights. The first night I stayed in the Mirror Room. It was definately a strange experience but great fun. I wouldnt have wanted to spend more than one night because the room was very small and claustrophobic but was great for one night.The second night I moved to the Two Lions rooms. How awesome. An enormous room with 2 lion cages hanging from the ceiling. The bathroom was excellent with a roll top bath and balcony.Personally I loved the location of the hotel. It was situated just off one of the best shopping areas in Berlin. I felt safe the whole time I was in this beautiful city.Its a very laid back place to stay. Its not a regular hotel - more of an art gallery. Yes, it does have bare pipes - some rooms dont have showers or toilets - towels are in short supply - no room service etc. etc. But then if thats what you want check-in to the Holiday Inn! Breakfast though was superb and there is a mini bar in reception.We had superb time. All you need is an open mind and a sense of fun.Highly recommend for a fun and unusual experience at a fair price. But go for the Two Lions room - its the most expensive of the suites but definately the best.Loved it. 
