<Author>greggoak
<Content>Unique experience I found out about this hotel in the Time Out Berlin guide, which recommended it as a quirky and unique experience. That it was! My partner and I stayed at the Arcotel Velvet for several days, and then traveled on to Moscow (the Velvet is very well located and certainly wins points for style - service was quite minimal). Our flight schedule required us to spend one more night in Berlin on our return journey from Moscow, so we decided to pick someplace a relatively close drive from the airport and more interesting than the usual room with bed, armoire, TV and mini-bar setup. We chose one of the more user-friendly rooms (the Temple room), although even in this one I think staying there more than a few nights would have become rather tedious. You can put up with awkward inconveniences in the name of art and adventure for a night or two (or three), but beyond that, I'd imagine being ready to move on. The staff was very friendly and very casual. It felt like we were guests in an artsy/hippie communal house. And the location is very quiet (not a busy street), but just a short walk to plenty of restaurants and cafes. Come here with no expectations other than to be surprised and you'll enjoy yourself. 
