<Author>Meltwaterfalls
<Content>Great experince I really enjoyed my stay here, it was a very individual experience, and very reflective of the artistic trends in Berlin. We stayed in the Castle Room, which was very good, it was the first room designed in the Hotel. The Castle room and Cloud room are actually in a separate part of the building from the main part of the Hotel, they share a bath room and small kitchen dinning room so if there is a small group of you this may be a great opportunity to have a self contained unit. The bed was surprisingly comfortable, I thought that comfort may have been overlooked in favour of style, but this was not the case.The only entertainment in the room was a very high quality stereo and CDs created by the designer of the hotel, to be honest I liked this, I have had enough of sitting in Hotels and watching 24 hour business news, or attempting to decipher some of the local language TV, so it was nice to just be able to relax. The music may not be to everyone鈥檚 taste though, if you like Warp Records or similar stuff then perhaps you will be presently surprised.I did take photos of the rooms but they asked you not to reproduce them anywhere, and to be honest the photo's on the official website are much better than any of mine and are very accurate. We were also told that we can walk around the main Hotel and Gallery and have a look in the rooms if we wanted to see more, but we were a little pressed for time so didn't take this up.All in all a great Hotel and one of the best ways to experience Berlin's art scene. 
