<Content>We loved our friend/family-friendly apartment I travelled with 3 friends and we stayed in the Castle and Cloud rooms. It was a self-contained apartment in a residential block behind the main lodge. This was better than anticipated and gave us our own area to hang-out in. We had no problems with noisy neighbours and unlike other reviewers, there was a functioning stereo in the Castle room with several of the lodges own ambient CD's.I was worried the Castle room may be too colourful but it was totally fab. Although it is a double room they provided us with 2 single duvets and it was comfortable and no problem sharing with a friend.The kitchenette was great for getting together whilst planning our days or disecting our nights. It has a fridge and a couple of small hobs so not for a gourmet feast but perfect for snacking.The bathroom was clean and modern and the shower was powerful.There were a few really nice restaurants and bakeries nearby. The second night we took a taxi to find somewhere more lively. The lodge is only a couple of minutes from the Ku'damm. The tour buses run along it but leave from the other end. It is a pleasant 15-20 minute walk (which would've taken us a lot longer if it wasn't Sunday and the shops were closed).I loved this place and would definately consider coming back. This apartment didn't have an overtly sexual undertone unlike some of the other rooms. It is in a peaceful and sedate area so the only drawback is if you want lively night-life on your doorstep. 
