<Author>persistent
<Content>Avoid hot weather I have to agree with the other reviewer; that is that although we were glad to have seen it we would not return. The hotel is very imaginatively decorated and the staff are lovely people, no problem with speaking English and very informal and friendly. breakfast was fine, the usual range of bread cheese meatsand cereal plus eggs. They were also flexible about time for breakfast and allowed us to leave our luggage in the hotel and collect it later. There are interesting public areas and an art gallery. the location is good and the lack of normal reception hours was not noticeable.We had 3 rooms, one single ,2 double. The single room had no shower and if the person staying there was alone it would have been necessary to shower on another floor. ok not a disaster but this was not youth hostel price.All our rooms were on top floor and the heatwave had been raging for 8 weeks so as heat rises our floor was hot and did not cool down completely at night, need I say there was no air conditioning?One of the 3 rooms, landscapes was Ok for temperature because it was on the shadier side of the hotel and we opened the windows . (we also had a bath and shower)but the single room Terra? had few opening windows and was on the sunny side. The other double room , electric wallpapers also got unbearably hot but had a kitchen and shower. In all 3 rooms art takes precedence over practicality and comfort .Despite the heat there was no effort made to improve air circulation,;windows were closed by the chambermaid and the floor was sealed by a heavy door at the head of the stairs. Although management were very unusual the chambermaid seemed the usual grumpy overworked woman just needing to complete her tasks. certainly no sleeping in on check out morning!My other main concern was that the beds being made of foam were uncomfortable. This was less an issue for the younger members of our group and they felt that the hotel was great for young creative people. However even they would like to try a more conventional but more comfortable place next time.I understand that we experienced freak weather conditions and staff told me that the hotel stays pleasantly warm in the winter months. 
